---
description: Mobile-only responsive work must not change desktop (lg+) layout
alwaysApply: true
---

# Mobile vs desktop (Paragon)

Unless the user **explicitly** asks to change desktop, treat all layout work as **mobile-only** (`< lg`, 1024px).

## Required pattern: desktop-first + `max-lg:`

- **Default (unprefixed) classes = desktop** — match existing `lg` specs.
- **Mobile overrides only** via `max-lg:` — never the other way around.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — mobile base bleeds into desktop unless every prop has lg: reset
<section className="h-[852px] lg:h-[894px]">
<div className="flex justify-between lg:block">

// ✅ GOOD — desktop is base; mobile adds max-lg: only
<section className="h-[894px] max-lg:h-[852px]">
<div className="max-lg:flex max-lg:justify-between">
```

## Markup and assets

- Different copy/line breaks: two blocks — `max-lg:hidden` (desktop) and `hidden max-lg:block` (mobile).
- Different backgrounds/images: separate wrappers — `max-lg:block lg:hidden` vs `hidden lg:block`.
- Do not share one `Image`/`className` when mobile and desktop differ materially.

## Before finishing

- Confirm no unprefixed class was added that changes desktop without a matching desktop spec.
- Do not remove or weaken existing `lg:` / desktop layout unless asked.
- Tablet (`md`/`sm`) follows mobile unless the user says otherwise.
